[[Scorpia]] is a powerful [[Wilderness boss]] capable of [[poisoning]] her opponents starting at 20 damage as well as hitting up to 16 with [[melee]]. Her lair, located beneath the [[Scorpion Pit]], is filled with many [[Scorpia's offspring (monster)|Scorpia's offspring]], which use accurate ranged attacks with a max hit of 2 and inflict poison starting at 6 damage.

Once Scorpia reaches 99 health or lower, she will summon two [[Scorpia's guardian|Scorpia's guardians]] which will continually heal Scorpia when within 3 tiles of her until they are killed or despawned. The guardians will not respawn if killed, and will despawn if they are too far away to heal Scorpia for 15 seconds.

An effective strategy is to exploit her low [[Magic#Monster_magic_defence|magic defence]] by using [[Ice Barrage|ice barrage]] to freeze her ([[Ice Burst|ice burst]], [[Ice Blitz|ice blitz]] or [[entangle]] will also work fine), staying out of melee range while attacking her with magic, and praying [[Protect from Missiles]] to prevent damage from Scorpia's offspring. Once her guardians spawn, players should wait until Scorpia is about to become unfrozen, then quickly freeze both guardians and lure Scorpia far away from them. This should cause the guardians to despawn, allowing Scorpia to be easily finished off.

==Tips==
* If you are comfortable with it, set NPC attack options to "always right click" so you don't accidentally target the [[Scorpia's offspring (monster)|offspring]], as this hinders your movement and wastes runes and Scorpion slayer kills. Alternatively, a plugin available in any approved third-party [[game client]] called "Menu Entry Swapper" will allow customizable left/shift click settings, allowing you to set the left-click option of the offspring as "Walk here".
* Consider using longrange/defensive casting. Standing further away makes positioning easier when Scorpia unfreezes.
* A good way to lure Scorpia away from her guardians is to position yourself at the side where you will be luring her just before she reaches half hp and freezing the healers immediately as they spawn. This requires careful timing, as Scorpia should ideally unfreeze very soon after you freeze both the guardians.
* If using ancient magicks, you may utilise manual casting of blood spells to heal yourself when Scorpia is frozen and minions are not around.
* Lower levelled players not using a toxic weapon may also try to poison Scorpia with a couple casts of [[Smoke spells|Smoke blitz/barrage]] when starting the kill for a little bit of extra damage.
* The guardians give highly reduced experience. Do not rely on experience drops to see whether you hit them.

==Suggested skills==
*{{SCP|Magic|78+}} for [[Trident of the swamp]]
*{{SCP|Prayer|40+}} for [[Protect from Missiles]]

==Equipment==
The setup primarily consists of only '''taking 3 or 4 expensive items''' as this [[boss]] resides in a [[multi-combat area]] in '''level 50+ [[Wilderness]]''', meaning player killers may quickly kill off-guard players.

Scorpia is not immune to [[venom]] and [[poison]]; therefore, using a [[trident of the swamp]] will do some additional damage over the course of the kill. Due to her low magic defence, a minimally geared player will rarely miss, therefore magic damage and prayer bonus should be prioritised over magic accuracy to reduce risk and prolong trips.

If bringing a [[powered staff]], a magic boost such as a [[Magic potion]], [[Forgotten brew]], or [[Saturated heart|Saturated]]/[[Imbued heart]] will provide additional magic damage.

